":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default value of this property is an expression that evaluates to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"standard","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Set this property to ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to reset it to the default value.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can set this property to an expression containing any of the following:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Constant "},{"code":"MLNHillshadeMethod","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" values"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Any of the following constant string values:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"standard","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": The legacy hillshade method."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"basic","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": Basic hillshade. Uses a simple physics model where the reflected"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"light intensity is proportional to the cosine of the angle between the incident"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"light and the surface normal. Similar to GDAL’s "},{"code":"gdaldem","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" default algorithm."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"combined","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": Hillshade algorithm whose intensity scales with slope. Similar"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to GDAL’s "},{"code":"gdaldem","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"code":"-combined","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" option."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"igor"},{"type":"text","text":": Hillshade algorithm which tries to minimize effects on other map"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"features beneath. Similar to GDAL’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"t